  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Growing cells were incubated with 10 µM BrdU for one hour before trypsinization.",
    "Trypsinized cells were suspended in 65% PBS with 35% ethanol and fixed overnight at 4 °C.",
    "Fixed cells were denatured using HCl and then neutralized with borax before stained with fluorescent anti-BrdU antibodies for an hour, exactly as described previously 69.",
    "Nuclei were incubated in PBS containing 10 µg/ mL of propidium iodide (PI) and 40 µg/mL of RNaseA for 1 h. Stained cells were analyzed using an Accuri C6 plus flow cytometer (BD) and analyzed using the manufacturer's software.",
    "G2/M cell cycle assay."
  ],
